# lodor#7 never-gate-harder: disc 1 is present, the next-disc fetch FAILS (server
# unreachable, rc=3) -> the hook logs the honest decision, leaves the stub intact
# (no fake bytes), and still exits 0 — the game plays on the discs it has.
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): failed next-disc fetch never gates the launch
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u	FF7/D1.chd\nFF7/D2.chd\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D1.chd
sdfile Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT complete=0 discs_total=2 discs_present=1
engine 3|
engine 0|RESULT complete=0 discs_total=2 discs_present=1
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_file_empty Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
expect_log discs: next-disc fetch incomplete
